# burner-keys.registry — Claude Stem v2.0
#
# (Project renamed claude-foundations → Claude Stem at S99 pre-GA, 2026-05-03.)
#
# This registry tracks every burner ANTHROPIC_API_KEY ever issued during
# Plan 71 dogfood / smoke runs. Each entry records: key id, created_at,
# last_known_status (live/revoked), revocation_verified_at, scope.
#
# RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md Step 4 (burner-key revocation audit) requires that
# every entry in this file return 410 Gone or 403 Unauthorized when probed
# via the Anthropic console API. A single live (200) historical key blocks
# v2.0.0 release per spec L245.
#
# Format: TSV, one key per line:
#   key_id<TAB>created_at_iso<TAB>last_known_status<TAB>revocation_verified_at<TAB>scope
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# v2.0.0-rc1 + v2.0.0 GA cycle entries
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# (none — no burner keys were issued during the rc1 OR GA cycles)
#
# Rationale: SP08 T-7a (Lima E2E dogfood) used fixture-staged
# user-manifest.json + orchestration.json instead of executing the real
# onboarder Section A-E flow inside an `sp00-isolation-onboarder` image
# variant. CFF-S87-2 — which would have required a burner key for the
# real-onboarder run — was disposed STANDALONE for v2.0.x patch (absorbed
# into T-9 30-day GA observation window).
#
# v2.0.0 GA close (S99, 2026-05-03) was a rebrand + relicense + paperwork
# session — zero new burner keys issued, zero API calls to Anthropic
# beyond GitHub workflows (which use GHA-internal OIDC, not API keys).
#
# Result: v2.0.0 (rc1 + GA) ships with zero burner-key exposure surface.
# RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md Step 4 revocation audit is a documented NO-OP for
# both the rc1 and the GA cycles.
#
# v2.0.x patch / v2.1+ cycles must populate this file as keys are issued.
